# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorPath5
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had woken up early the next morning to the sound of knocking at her door, a small headache reminding her of the celebration from the night before."
    new "Sarah had woken up early the next morning to the sound of knocking at her door, a small headache reminding her of the celebration from the night before."

    old "Answering the door, she found Vaelen waiting for her."
    new "Answering the door, she found Vaelen waiting for her."

    old "To Sarah's surprise, Vaelen was alone. He was rarely alone."
    new "To Sarah's surprise, Vaelen was alone. He was rarely alone."

    old "We need to talk."
    new "We need to talk."

    old "Sarah didn't like the tone of his voice. It didn't sound like he was asking."
    new "Sarah didn't like the tone of his voice. It didn't sound like he was asking."

    old "Sarah closed the door to her room behind her."
    new "Sarah closed the door to her room behind her."

    old "Vaelen started to walk, motioning for her to keep up."
    new "Vaelen started to walk, motioning for her to keep up."

    old "She caught up to him and began to walk besides him, keeping pace."
    new "She caught up to him and began to walk besides him, keeping pace."

    old "You enjoyed the celebrations?"
    new "You enjoyed the celebrations?"

    old "I managed."
    new "I managed."

    old "She could see him smile."
    new "She could see him smile."

    old "There was something about his smile that had always unsettled her. It had taken her years before she finally realized what it was."
    new "There was something about his smile that had always unsettled her. It had taken her years before she finally realized what it was."

    old "He never smiled genuinely."
    new "He never smiled genuinely."

    old "It was a reflex he performed, but there was never anything real behind it."
    new "It was a reflex he performed, but there was never anything real behind it."

    old "The Mythran camp is in a bit of chaos after their prince was...well, you know."
    new "The Mythran camp is in a bit of chaos after their prince was...well, you know."

    old "Eaten by a demon, Sarah thought."
    new "Eaten by a demon, Sarah thought."

    old "Their commanders can't quite figure out whose supposed to be next in line for command."
    new "Their commanders can't quite figure out whose supposed to be next in line for command."

    old "Rest the poor bastard's soul, but it's not entirely unfortunate for us."
    new "Rest the poor bastard's soul, but it's not entirely unfortunate for us."

    old "Now that they're too busy arguing amongst themselves, none of them have really found the time to press us about occupying the western wing."
    new "Now that they're too busy arguing amongst themselves, none of them have really found the time to press us about occupying the western wing."

    old "Sarah kept walking besides him, listening."
    new "Sarah kept walking besides him, listening."

    old "The hall was emptied out, save for them. Most soldiers were likely still sleeping off the night before."
    new "The hall was emptied out, save for them. Most soldiers were likely still sleeping off the night before."

    old "But I don't know how long their discord will last, so I wanted to make our move now."
    new "But I don't know how long their discord will last, so I wanted to make our move now."

    old "Now?"
    new "Now?"

    old "You mean break open the royal vault?"
    new "You mean break open the royal vault?"

    old "Vaelen nodded."
    new "Vaelen nodded."

    old "Wouldn't it be better to bring an entire unit of soldiers?"
    new "Wouldn't it be better to bring an entire unit of soldiers?"

    old "I mean, breaking it open alone is one thing, but carrying out all the valuables..."
    new "I mean, breaking it open alone is one thing, but carrying out all the valuables..."

    old "Not exactly a job for two people."
    new "Not exactly a job for two people."

    old "Vaelen turned to her."
    new "Vaelen turned to her."

    old "Sarah, this isn't about stealing some chests of gold from an old family vault."
    new "Sarah, this isn't about stealing some chests of gold from an old family vault."

    old "There is a particular item in that room that I'm after, and I don't need an entire army of soldiers stomping around."
    new "There is a particular item in that room that I'm after, and I don't need an entire army of soldiers stomping around."

    old "Sarah had suspected there was more to his plan than simple avarice."
    new "Sarah had suspected there was more to his plan than simple avarice."

    old "What is it then?"
    new "What is it then?"

    old "It's a gem. Or a jewel of a sort. In fact, I don't exactly know what it looks like."
    new "It's a gem. Or a jewel of a sort. In fact, I don't exactly know what it looks like."

    old "If you don't know what it looks like, how will we know when we find it?"
    new "If you don't know what it looks like, how will we know when we find it?"

    old "Trust me, Sarah, when we find it you'll know. It has a very particular red glow to it. When you see it, you'll know."
    new "Trust me, Sarah, when we find it you'll know. It has a very particular red glow to it. When you see it, you'll know."

    old "Vaelen continued his pace, leading her further along the halls of the western wing, down towards the far side."
    new "Vaelen continued his pace, leading her further along the halls of the western wing, down towards the far side."

    old "There was nothing there but a dead end."
    new "There was nothing there but a dead end."

    old "Or so it seemed until Sarah watched Vaelen push a small button near the corner of one of the walls."
    new "Or so it seemed until Sarah watched Vaelen push a small button near the corner of one of the walls."

    old "As if appearing from thin air, the perfectly solid wall pulled back, revealing the entrance to a tunnel."
    new "As if appearing from thin air, the perfectly solid wall pulled back, revealing the entrance to a tunnel."

    old "No light came from it, only a gust of cold air."
    new "No light came from it, only a gust of cold air."

    old "Vaelen pulled a torch from the wall and held it up, leading the way."
    new "Vaelen pulled a torch from the wall and held it up, leading the way."

    old "How did you know how to find it?"
    new "How did you know how to find it?"

    old "I told you once before, a long time ago, that I know things."
    new "I told you once before, a long time ago, that I know things."

    old "You ask me how I know them, I wish I knew any better than you."
    new "You ask me how I know them, I wish I knew any better than you."

    old "Sometimes, in my life, things appear to me so obvious that I don't wonder how I know them, only how anyone else couldn't."
    new "Sometimes, in my life, things appear to me so obvious that I don't wonder how I know them, only how anyone else couldn't."

    old "This pathway is one of them. The gemstone another."
    new "This pathway is one of them. The gemstone another."

    old "Sarah felt as though something was crawling across her skin as she followed Vaelen deeper into the tunnel."
    new "Sarah felt as though something was crawling across her skin as she followed Vaelen deeper into the tunnel."

    old "The secret pathway quickly split apart into differing directions, with stairs leading up and down. The thing was like a maze."
    new "The secret pathway quickly split apart into differing directions, with stairs leading up and down. The thing was like a maze."

    old "But Vaelen didn't move through it as though it confused him. He moved as though he'd walked the path many times before."
    new "But Vaelen didn't move through it as though it confused him. He moved as though he'd walked the path many times before."

    old "Sarah knew her only chance of ever getting out of these tunnels was to keep up with Vaelen."
    new "Sarah knew her only chance of ever getting out of these tunnels was to keep up with Vaelen."

    old "As she followed him deeper into the tunnels, Sarah could feel the air growing colder still."
    new "As she followed him deeper into the tunnels, Sarah could feel the air growing colder still."

    old "Each step echoed out, seemingly forever."
    new "Each step echoed out, seemingly forever."

    old "Castle Reinmeer was no stranger to secret tunnels, and when Sarah had been a child, she had loved exploring every part of the castle."
    new "Castle Reinmeer was no stranger to secret tunnels, and when Sarah had been a child, she had loved exploring every part of the castle."

    old "In this place, it felt different."
    new "In this place, it felt different."

    old "Suffocating. Crushing. As though the weight of the entire palace was balanced on top of them."
    new "Suffocating. Crushing. As though the weight of the entire palace was balanced on top of them."

    old "Perhaps it was, Sarah realized as they went deeper."
    new "Perhaps it was, Sarah realized as they went deeper."

    old "Vaelen turned a corner, following him, Sarah suddenly found the room expanding in a every direction."
    new "Vaelen turned a corner, following him, Sarah suddenly found the room expanding in a every direction."

    old "A great open space in the midsts of this claustrophobic construct."
    new "A great open space in the midsts of this claustrophobic construct."

    old "For a moment, she felt disoriented as her eyes struggled to make sense of the thing she was looking at."
    new "For a moment, she felt disoriented as her eyes struggled to make sense of the thing she was looking at."

    old "It was hard to make out against the darkness."
    new "It was hard to make out against the darkness."

    old "A metal door, carefully decorated, cut into the wall."
    new "A metal door, carefully decorated, cut into the wall."

    old "The light of the torch did not so much touch it, as was absorbed by it, making everything around it darker."
    new "The light of the torch did not so much touch it, as was absorbed by it, making everything around it darker."

    old "Only when Sarah came closer did her eyes catch the nuances of the thing."
    new "Only when Sarah came closer did her eyes catch the nuances of the thing."

    old "Etched into the brown metal, a script in a language that appeared alien to her."
    new "Etched into the brown metal, a script in a language that appeared alien to her."

    old "The lines ran so thin and delicate. Carved into the metal, the lines were hard to make out from the sides."
    new "The lines ran so thin and delicate. Carved into the metal, the lines were hard to make out from the sides."

    old "Only looking directly at the vault's door could she see the cryptic texts."
    new "Only looking directly at the vault's door could she see the cryptic texts."

    old "Sarah could not read them, and still, they spoke to her of danger."
    new "Sarah could not read them, and still, they spoke to her of danger."

    old "I don't think this is safe."
    new "I don't think this is safe."

    old "She saw Vaelen transfixed, staring at the door, before finally speaking."
    new "She saw Vaelen transfixed, staring at the door, before finally speaking."

    old "You're right, it's not."
    new "You're right, it's not."

    old "It's very old. One of the first rooms ever constructed, back when Bagrad was still a backwater village."
    new "It's very old. One of the first rooms ever constructed, back when Bagrad was still a backwater village."

    old "It will likely sit here till the end of days."
    new "It will likely sit here till the end of days."

    old "Nothing should exist for so long."
    new "Nothing should exist for so long."

    old "An old metal and an old language, each long lost to history. Even I don't know much more than that."
    new "An old metal and an old language, each long lost to history. Even I don't know much more than that."

    old "How do we open it?"
    new "How do we open it?"

    old "For us, the door will open itself."
    new "For us, the door will open itself."

    old "He gestured, and as if by magic, the door answered his motion."
    new "He gestured, and as if by magic, the door answered his motion."

    old "The solid door began to part."
    new "The solid door began to part."

    old "A grinding sound, like metal scraping metal, rang out through the tunnels. The echo made it feel like the sound was in Sarah's body."
    new "A grinding sound, like metal scraping metal, rang out through the tunnels. The echo made it feel like the sound was in Sarah's body."

    old "How did you do that?"
    new "How did you do that?"

    old "The gate only permits entry to those it wants."
    new "The gate only permits entry to those it wants."

    old "Bagrad's royal family foolish believed that meant themselves, but the door has a mind of its own, and it decides itself who it grants entry."
    new "Bagrad's royal family foolish believed that meant themselves, but the door has a mind of its own, and it decides itself who it grants entry."

    old "A door with a mind of its own. Sarah thought she couldn't be more unnerved by the thing."
    new "A door with a mind of its own. Sarah thought she couldn't be more unnerved by the thing."

    old "Sarah watched as Vaelen strode forward, entering the vault."
    new "Sarah watched as Vaelen strode forward, entering the vault."

    old "She quickly followed."
    new "She quickly followed."

    old "Once inside the vault, Sarah felt a change in the air."
    new "Once inside the vault, Sarah felt a change in the air."

    old "Its temprature was much the same as before, but there seemed a strange humidity here, and a smell she couldn't quite place."
    new "Its temprature was much the same as before, but there seemed a strange humidity here, and a smell she couldn't quite place."

    old "Out before her, as far as the light of the torch could reach, there were items piled up."
    new "Out before her, as far as the light of the torch could reach, there were items piled up."

    old "In the midsts of everything, countless objects glittering, reflecting the light."
    new "In the midsts of everything, countless objects glittering, reflecting the light."

    old "Sarah tried to take it all in, but it seemed overwhelming."
    new "Sarah tried to take it all in, but it seemed overwhelming."

    old "How far does this go on for?"
    new "How far does this go on for?"

    old "I have no idea, Sarah."
    new "I have no idea, Sarah."

    old "Can you grab that?"
    new "Can you grab that?"

    old "Vaelen gestured towards a lamp that hung besides the door."
    new "Vaelen gestured towards a lamp that hung besides the door."

    old "Despite there being no flame, it cast a sickly pale white blue light."
    new "Despite there being no flame, it cast a sickly pale white blue light."

    old "Sarah grabbed the lantern and held it up."
    new "Sarah grabbed the lantern and held it up."

    old "I'll go left here, you take the right side. Just keep going till you find the stone."
    new "I'll go left here, you take the right side. Just keep going till you find the stone."

    old "It frustrated Sarah that she still didn't fully understand what she was looking for."
    new "It frustrated Sarah that she still didn't fully understand what she was looking for."

    old "And I'll know it when I see it?"
    new "And I'll know it when I see it?"

    old "When you find the stone, don't touch it. Call for me and I'll take care of the rest."
    new "When you find the stone, don't touch it. Call for me and I'll take care of the rest."

    old "With that, Sarah watched Vaelen take off."
    new "With that, Sarah watched Vaelen take off."

    old "Sarah began her own exploration, walking through the piled up crates and mountains of gold."
    new "Sarah began her own exploration, walking through the piled up crates and mountains of gold."

    old "How much wealth, she imagined, sat here simply boxed up. Enough to change a thousand lives forever, but here, too trivial even to take out of the box."
    new "How much wealth, she imagined, sat here simply boxed up. Enough to change a thousand lives forever, but here, too trivial even to take out of the box."

    old "Walking through the vault brought about an odd feelig."
    new "Walking through the vault brought about an odd feelig."

    old "All these things, unseen, untouched and unnoticed."
    new "All these things, unseen, untouched and unnoticed."

    old "What did art mean, or wealth, when it just sat here, hidden from the world. Other than the Shah, who ever even looked at these things? Did he even?"
    new "What did art mean, or wealth, when it just sat here, hidden from the world. Other than the Shah, who ever even looked at these things? Did he even?"

    old "Once, artists and labourers poured their sweat and tears into creating these masterworks, all so they could end up here, forgotten."
    new "Once, artists and labourers poured their sweat and tears into creating these masterworks, all so they could end up here, forgotten."

    old "Perhaps, Sarah thought, it might be better if they were looted, thrown back out into the world."
    new "Perhaps, Sarah thought, it might be better if they were looted, thrown back out into the world."

    old "Sarah slowly followed her path, illuminating it with the lantern."
    new "Sarah slowly followed her path, illuminating it with the lantern."

    old "Would she even know it if she saw it?"
    new "Would she even know it if she saw it?"

    old "Sarah passed one artwork after the other. There was no time to stop and wonder."
    new "Sarah passed one artwork after the other. There was no time to stop and wonder."

    old "In the corner of her eyes, she recognizes something."
    new "In the corner of her eyes, she recognizes something."

    old "Sarah stops and turns towards the massive painting."
    new "Sarah stops and turns towards the massive painting."

    old "Her heart stops for a moment."
    new "Her heart stops for a moment."

    old "Depicted upon the canvas is the royal family of Rosanna. Her father. Her brother. And herself."
    new "Depicted upon the canvas is the royal family of Rosanna. Her father. Her brother. And herself."

    old "Her father sits towards the center, she and her brother by his side. Strong. Regal. Just as he had been in life."
    new "Her father sits towards the center, she and her brother by his side. Strong. Regal. Just as he had been in life."

    old "Sarah knew this painting well. It once had a prominent place in Castle Reinmeer."
    new "Sarah knew this painting well. It once had a prominent place in Castle Reinmeer."

    old "So often she had walked past it, observed it, traced its meticulous design."
    new "So often she had walked past it, observed it, traced its meticulous design."

    old "And now it was here."
    new "And now it was here."

    old "Sarah reached out, touching the frame of the painting as if to make sure it was real."
    new "Sarah reached out, touching the frame of the painting as if to make sure it was real."

    old "How did you end up here..."
    new "How did you end up here..."

    old "Looting, she had no doubt. The tribesmen must have seized it, and with no use for art, sold it off to some merchant, passing hands until one day it dissapeared into this vault."
    new "Looting, she had no doubt. The tribesmen must have seized it, and with no use for art, sold it off to some merchant, passing hands until one day it dissapeared into this vault."

    old "What a prize it must have been, the painting of the last royal family of Rosanna."
    new "What a prize it must have been, the painting of the last royal family of Rosanna."

    old "She couldn't take it with her, yet, it also felt wrong to her to leave it behind. It wasn't theirs, it belonged to her."
    new "She couldn't take it with her, yet, it also felt wrong to her to leave it behind. It wasn't theirs, it belonged to her."

    old "Sarah committed  the painting to mind. Then, she swung her sword across it, slashing the frame in half."
    new "Sarah committed  the painting to mind. Then, she swung her sword across it, slashing the frame in half."

    old "The old material of the canvas tore easily."
    new "The old material of the canvas tore easily."

    old "As she turned to resume her search, a glimmer of crimson caught her eye near the end of the path."
    new "As she turned to resume her search, a glimmer of crimson caught her eye near the end of the path."

    old "Sarah rushed forward, fearing to lose sight of it, but not long after found herself coming upon the object."
    new "Sarah rushed forward, fearing to lose sight of it, but not long after found herself coming upon the object."

    old "It was as Vaelen had said a stone that shone with light of crimson, but it was also not quite a gemstone or a ruby."
    new "It was as Vaelen had said a stone that shone with light of crimson, but it was also not quite a gemstone or a ruby."

    old "The light swirled within it. The colours softly shifted, from crimson to other variations of the colour, exploring patterns Sarah had never seen before in her life."
    new "The light swirled within it. The colours softly shifted, from crimson to other variations of the colour, exploring patterns Sarah had never seen before in her life."

    old "Don't touch it."
    new "Don't touch it."

    old "She had to remind herself, because the object seemed to almost reach out to her, begging to be seized."
    new "She had to remind herself, because the object seemed to almost reach out to her, begging to be seized."

    old "Sarah nearly turned to call out to Vaelen, only for the light around her to begin to fade."
    new "Sarah nearly turned to call out to Vaelen, only for the light around her to begin to fade."

    old "There was still a light, but it turned cold and grey, and the sounds around her grew muted."
    new "There was still a light, but it turned cold and grey, and the sounds around her grew muted."

    old "Something arose from the shadows, swirling and shifting. Something familiar to Sarah."
    new "Something arose from the shadows, swirling and shifting. Something familiar to Sarah."

    old "Sarah pulled out her sword and held it up in the direction of the creature."
    new "Sarah pulled out her sword and held it up in the direction of the creature."

    old "It looked similar to the thing she had killed in the throne room."
    new "It looked similar to the thing she had killed in the throne room."

    old "And yet, it appeared somehow different."
    new "And yet, it appeared somehow different."

    old "Stepping forward, she swiped her blade horizontally through the creature."
    new "Stepping forward, she swiped her blade horizontally through the creature."

    old "The blade caught nothing but air."
    new "The blade caught nothing but air."

    old "That won't work. My nature is not quite so similar."
    new "That won't work. My nature is not quite so similar."

    old "Sarah felt the blood in her veins freeze."
    new "Sarah felt the blood in her veins freeze."

    old "The thing could speak."
    new "The thing could speak."

    old "What...what are you?!"
    new "What...what are you?!"

    old "Sarah did her best to hide the fear that invaded her voice."
    new "Sarah did her best to hide the fear that invaded her voice."

    old "An old friend, Sarah."
    new "An old friend, Sarah."

    old "How do you know my name?"
    new "How do you know my name?"

    old "You told me once, and I don't forget a name."
    new "You told me once, and I don't forget a name."

    old "A sense of revulsion grew in Sarah as she watched the thing move through the air, its voice uttering her name."
    new "A sense of revulsion grew in Sarah as she watched the thing move through the air, its voice uttering her name."

    old "I would have remembered meeting a demon like yourself."
    new "I would have remembered meeting a demon like yourself."

    old "A hissing sound emerged from the thing. It took a moment for Sarah to realize it passed for laughter."
    new "A hissing sound emerged from the thing. It took a moment for Sarah to realize it passed for laughter."

    old "Not a demon. Merely a humble spirit."
    new "Not a demon. Merely a humble spirit."

    old "And you would be surprised what people in this world forget sometimes."
    new "And you would be surprised what people in this world forget sometimes."

    old "Sarah stomped her metal boot on the ground and raised her sword again."
    new "Sarah stomped her metal boot on the ground and raised her sword again."

    old "Enough of your cryptic bullshit!"
    new "Enough of your cryptic bullshit!"

    old "For a moment, the thing was silent."
    new "For a moment, the thing was silent."

    old "I must confess, I liked the other one more."
    new "I must confess, I liked the other one more."

    old "Regardless, Sarah, we meet under auspicious conditions."
    new "Regardless, Sarah, we meet under auspicious conditions."

    old "I didn't come here to commune with unholy beasts."
    new "I didn't come here to commune with unholy beasts."

    old "Did you not come here seeking a stone of crimson?"
    new "Did you not come here seeking a stone of crimson?"

    old "The creature's nature unsettled Sarah, but not nearly as much as how it appeared to know things beyond what it should."
    new "The creature's nature unsettled Sarah, but not nearly as much as how it appeared to know things beyond what it should."

    old "How did you know that?"
    new "How did you know that?"

    old "The spirit's body twisted, its smokey body reshaping as it danced on the air."
    new "The spirit's body twisted, its smokey body reshaping as it danced on the air."

    old "You have found it."
    new "You have found it."

    old "Sarah could see the red crimson glow of the stone, softly humming."
    new "Sarah could see the red crimson glow of the stone, softly humming."

    old "But I come to you bearing a warning."
    new "But I come to you bearing a warning."

    old "A warning?"
    new "A warning?"

    old "Your master. The-one-who-calls-himself-Vaelen. He seeks the stone, but you must not give it to him."
    new "Your master. The-one-who-calls-himself-Vaelen. He seeks the stone, but you must not give it to him."

    old "How could it know such things."
    new "How could it know such things."

    old "Because this stone is what is called a fate stone. And the-one-who-calls-himself-Vaelen, he will seek to wield it against you."
    new "Because this stone is what is called a fate stone. And the-one-who-calls-himself-Vaelen, he will seek to wield it against you."

    old "Against me? Vaelen is my ally."
    new "Against me? Vaelen is my ally."

    old "The spirit laughed at her."
    new "The spirit laughed at her."

    old "He is many things, but he is not your friend."
    new "He is many things, but he is not your friend."

    old "And you are?"
    new "And you are?"

    old "We have been before. We can be again."
    new "We have been before. We can be again."

    old "One more riddle out of you and I swear I'll find a way to hurt you, even if it means bringing down the palace on your head."
    new "One more riddle out of you and I swear I'll find a way to hurt you, even if it means bringing down the palace on your head."

    old "Forgive me, Sarah."
    new "Forgive me, Sarah."

    old "She watched as its body shifted again. At parts, she could look right through it."
    new "She watched as its body shifted again. At parts, she could look right through it."

    old "Now tell me."
    new "Now tell me."

    old "Why would I take the word of some vile spirit over that of my commander?"
    new "Why would I take the word of some vile spirit over that of my commander?"

    old "Because your master has been gifted with sight-beyond-sight."
    new "Because your master has been gifted with sight-beyond-sight."

    old "And he fears what he has seen."
    new "And he fears what he has seen."

    old "When he is alone, he weeps for what destiny has in store for him."
    new "When he is alone, he weeps for what destiny has in store for him."

    old "He believes that the stone will save him from the pull of destiny."
    new "He believes that the stone will save him from the pull of destiny."

    old "What does the stone do?"
    new "What does the stone do?"

    old "The stone permits him to break free from the chain of fate that drags him towards his inevitable end and the pit that awaits him."
    new "The stone permits him to break free from the chain of fate that drags him towards his inevitable end and the pit that awaits him."

    old "And why should I care for any of this?"
    new "And why should I care for any of this?"

    old "He is my friend, he has done nothing but support me when nobody else would. Why should I not help him?"
    new "He is my friend, he has done nothing but support me when nobody else would. Why should I not help him?"

    old "Because the blade he seeks to divert, is yours."
    new "Because the blade he seeks to divert, is yours."

    old "Sarah stared at the spirit. For a time, she didn't know what to say."
    new "Sarah stared at the spirit. For a time, she didn't know what to say."

    old "Lies."
    new "Lies."

    old "You can't possibly know the future."
    new "You can't possibly know the future."

    old "And yet I do. As does Vaelen. The only one who is blind, is you. But you need not be."
    new "And yet I do. As does Vaelen. The only one who is blind, is you. But you need not be."

    old "Seize the stone, hide it from him."
    new "Seize the stone, hide it from him."

    old "And why would you tell me any of this? What game do you play at?"
    new "And why would you tell me any of this? What game do you play at?"

    old "No game, Sarah."
    new "No game, Sarah."

    old "I told you, we are old friends."
    new "I told you, we are old friends."

